/L_{\\gamma} \\lesssim 5 \\times 10^{-4}$) would\ndisfavor leptonic models for the gamma-ray emission. Our model can also be\napplied to other astrophysical environments with radiative shocks, including\nType IIn supernovae and colliding winds in massive star binaries.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Nov 2016 19:20:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-02-21"}
